    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="106"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72111/1073½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: As I intimated to you, I gave the
                    matter very serious thought when the question of the submarines was brought up.
                    I feel that it is really our duty (in the <hi rend="underline">spirit</hi>, at
                    any rate, of the <hi rend="italic">Alabama</hi> decision) to prevent submarines
                    being shipped from this country even in parts, and I hope that you will find a
                    way of checking and preventing this if it is contemplated.</p>
                <p>Always</p>
                <p>Cordially and faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
